<article>
	<header>
	<h1><a href="http://foodsense.is/blog/recipe-amys-topopo-salad">Recipe: Amy&#8217;s Topopo Salad</a></h1>
		</header>
		
	<div class="group">
					<p>Last week, Amy shared <a href="http://foodsense.is/blog/amys-monologue">her journey</a> to a plant-based life with us. Today, she shares a veganized version of her favorite meal, from her favorite restaurant in college - The Topopo Salad from El Azteco. </p>

<p>From Amy:</p><blockquote><p>“Topopo” means volcano, and as prepared at &#8220;El Az&#8221;, this is a huge salad for two people.&nbsp; The Topopo Salad is presented with the salad on top of the nacho base in a big pointed mound (the volcano.)&nbsp; You could add 2.5 oz vegan chicken, if you&#8217;d like.</p>
</blockquote>

<p>&nbsp;</p>
		<p><a href="http://foodsense.is/blog/recipe-amys-topopo-salad">Continue reading &raquo;</a></p>	</div>
		
